source.g: “Goods” are tangible products that physically exist.
Goods are categorized as “capital goods and consumer goods”.
Goods are categorized as “............ goods and consumer goods”.
Goods are categorized as “capital goods and ............... goods”.
“Capital Goods” are machinery, equipment, tools and other physical goods that are used in the production of other products. They are sold to businesses.
“Consumer Goods” are further categorized as “Consumer durables” and “Consumer non-durables”. Consumer goods are sold to “general public”.
“Consumer durables” are physical goods that last through repeated uses. They are sold to the “general public.” e.g. Cars, smartphones...etc.
“Consumer non-durables” are physical goods that need to be used shortly after the purchase. e.g. fresh vegetables, milk, cosmetics...etc.
Which type of goods can last through repeated uses?
“Services” are intangible products that often have visible results. e.g haircut, dental treatment...etc.
“Commercial services” are offered to other businesses. e.g. accounting services, consulting services, IT solutions...etc.
“Personal services” are offered to individual buyers. e.g. private lessons, haircuts, health services..etc.

REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
Individuals often start up businesses to generate profit and to enjoy keeping their income for themselves.
REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
“Being their own boss” or to enjoy the freedom of arranging the business life with flexibity and autonomy is another reason for starting up a business.
REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
Sometimes social or economic conditions, such as redundancy or unemployment, can lead people to starting up their own businesses.
REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
Individuals may choose to start up a business simply for self-actualization proving that they can be successful.
REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
Individuals may decide to turn their passions or hobbies into a business to keep doing what they enjoy doing as a job.
REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
Some entrepreneurs decide to start up a business after they spot a gap in the market with the purpose of enjoying “first-movers advantages”.
REASONS FOR STARTING UP A BUSINESS
Employees always work with the risk of loosing their jobs. They may decide to work as the boss of their own business for stability.
